Analysis.name: Withdrawal due to adverse event
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc:
Randomziation and distribuition of intervention centrally performed in hospital pharmacies.

Quote: "Randomisation was performed in hospital pharmacies in blocks of four."

Quote: "Trial drugs or placebo were dispensed by the hospital pharmacies using separate randomisation schedules [...]."

Baseline characteristics do not suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Participants unaware of received intervention. Blinding of trial personnel delivering intervention likely. Appropiate analysis.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Two patients of AZA group excluded. One of them could depend on its true value. Regarding small size of study, impact on outcome likely.
Overall.bias.support: Due to some concerns regarding missing outcome data and unavailability of protocol.

Analysis.name: Withdrawal due to adverse event
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: Randomization by "pseudorandom numbers generated by scientific calculator." No information on concealment of allocation. Disease duration at baseline significantly higher in azathioprine group.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int:
Patients blinded to the intervention. Quote: "The drugs were provided by a single coordinator to the patients in identical blister packs."

People delivering intervention unblinded. Quote: "The treatment physician was aware of the drug treatment."

Exclusion of five (two placebo, three azathioprine) patients due to documented reasons. Quote: "Five patients were excluded because of noncompliance and violation of treatment protocol (use of other medication)."

Apporpiate analysis used. Quote: "Clinical outcome was compared [...] on an intention-to-treat basis."
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Exclusion of five (two placebo, three azathioprine) patients due to noncompliance and violation of treatment protocol (use of other medication). Reasons for noncompliance were not provided.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Outcome assessor aware of intervention received. Unlikely, knowledge of intervention received could have affected outcome assessment.
Overall.bias.support: Due to insufficient information on concealment of allocation and unavailable protocol.

Analysis.name: Withdrawal due to adverse event
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc:
Randomization by "pseudorandom numbers ranging from 0-1, generated by scientific calculator."

No information on concealment of allocation.

Baseline characteristics do not suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int:
Participants unaware of intervention received. Trial personnel aware of intervention received. Appropiate analysis.

Quote: "[...] identical matched placebo drugs [...]"
Quote: "The drugs were provided by a single coordinator (V.K.) to the patients in identical blister packs."
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Results for this outcome was available for all randomized patients.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo:
Outcome assessors unaware of intervention received.

Quote: "[...] double-blind trial."
Overall.bias.support: Due to no information on concealment of allocation and unavailabilitiy of protocol.

Analysis.name: Withdrawal due to adverse event
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc:
Quote: "Sixteen patients were randomized to oral administration of either azathioprine or cyclosporin [...] ."

Quote: "Both groups were comparable in demographic and disease characteristics."

No information on concealment of allocation.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: No information on blinding and analysis used.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Results for this outcome available for all randomized participants.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: No information on methods of outcome assessment.
Overall.bias.support: No information on blinding, outcome assessment, and used analysis.

Analysis.name: Withdrawal due to adverse event
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc:
Computer generated randomization. Quote: "The randomization was based on a computer generated scheme that assigned the eligible patient to the next randomization."

No information on concealment of allocation.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Both participants and trial personnel aware of the intervention received. Withdrawal consistent with standard care. Analysis appropiate.
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Results for this outcome was available for all randomized patients.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Outcome assessor aware of intervention received. Unlikely, knowledge of intervention received could have effected outcome assessment.
Overall.bias.support: Due to insufficient information on concealment of allocation and unavailable protocol.

Analysis.name: Withdrawal due to adverse event
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc:
Centralized, computer-based randomization. Quote: "Patients were randomised using computer generated random numbers via a centralized randomisation service."

Concealment of allocation in sealed envelopes. Quote: "The allocation sequence was concealed in envelopes."

Baseline characteristics do not suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int:
Both participants and trial personnel aware of intervention received. Analysis was appropiate.

Quote: "We conducted our analyses based on the intention-to-treat principle including all patients randomised who received at least one dose of the allocated study drug."
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Results for this outcome available for all randomized participants.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Outcome assessor aware of intervention received. Unlikely, knowledge of intervention received could have effected outcome assessment.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: Prospectively registered protocol. Outcome reported as registered.
Overall.bias.support: Due to low risk of bias in all domains.
